    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nWrite a program where the `Painter` paints horizontal stripes.\r\n\r\n1. In your `custom.py` file, create the `move_and_paint_path(color)` function definition that will have the `Painter` paint a continuous line.\r\n2. Call the necessary functions and `Painter` methods to create the striped pattern.\r\n   - **Hint:** Ensure the `Painter` moves correctly between rows by adding appropriate turns and movements after each stripe.\r\n\r\n**Bonus Challenge:** Can you make the program more efficient by putting repeated function calls and `Painter` methods in new user-defined functions?\r\n\r\n**Reminder:** Make sure you import your `custom.py` file and save it to your backpack after adding any new functions!\r\n\r\n   \r\n::: details [**Need help with your algorithm?**]\r\nHere is one approach to solving this problem.\r\n\r\n```\r\nwhile the Painter has paint\r\n  if the Painter can move \r\n    paint\r\n    move\r\n```\r\n:::\r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n# ADD import custom BELOW\n\n# Create Painter object\nkai = Painter()\n\n# Function to turn right\ndef turn_right():\n    kai.turn_left()\n    kai.turn_left()\n    kai.turn_left()\n\n# Function to move forward while possible\ndef move_while_can():\n    while kai.can_move():\n        kai.move()\n\n# Function to take all the paint\ndef take_all_paint():\n  while kai.is_on_bucket():\n    kai.take_paint()\n\n# ADD DEFINITION FOR move_and_paint_path(color) FUNCTION IN custom.py\n     \n# ADD FUNCTION CALLS TO COMPLETE THE STRIPE PATTERN\ntake_all_paint()\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
